People often say, well, that sort of stuff is sort of easy for monks.

396
00:38:27,878 --> 00:38:29,139
It's difficult for lay people.

397
00:38:30,081 --> 00:38:32,643
Well, ideally, it is easy for monks.

398
00:38:32,663 --> 00:38:34,204
That's the whole idea of an institution.

399
00:38:34,764 --> 00:38:36,146
That's what the Buddha set up.

400
00:38:36,186 --> 00:38:38,188
He set up this institution to make it easy.

401
00:38:38,849 --> 00:38:40,030
He said, leave all that.

402
00:38:40,409 --> 00:38:42,371
He said, don't, you know, just get out of all that.

403
00:38:42,753 --> 00:38:47,416
Find yourself a little hut out there in a forest and just go for it.

404
00:38:49,168 --> 00:38:59,844
So the problem with lay life, the problem with living in society, especially in this one, is that everybody around you is doing exactly the opposite.

405
00:39:02,148 --> 00:39:12,742
I mean, if we were living in a more homogenous society, say like some of these Muslim societies, where if you said, well, I'm going to pray five times a day, they'd all say, fine, they might join in.

406
00:39:13,905 --> 00:39:18,871
If you said, well, I'm just going to meditate now half an hour at work, they'd be a nutter.

407
00:39:19,543 --> 00:39:21,385
And that's it.

408
00:39:21,786 --> 00:39:24,128
In this society, you're right up against the grain of it.

409
00:39:24,188 --> 00:39:28,795
Very few people really, you know, they just haven't got it.

410
00:39:29,315 --> 00:39:31,297
So, of course, it's very difficult.

411
00:39:31,317 --> 00:39:31,958
Very difficult.

412
00:39:35,161 --> 00:39:38,766
But that doesn't mean to say that we can't keep working at it.

413
00:39:39,407 --> 00:39:44,391
And also, you know, where there's a difficulty, there is that extra effort.

414
00:39:45,052 --> 00:39:49,297
And when you make that extra effort, you do get that extra comeback.

415
00:39:49,952 --> 00:39:52,561
It's just like when you sit in meditation.

416
00:39:53,043 --> 00:39:59,929
If you can just hang on in there through the restlessness or through the anxiety, then you get that benefit.

417
00:40:01,445 --> 00:40:27,134
So, again, it's a case of being in a situation where you feel it's against your spiritual life, it's actually something the people around you aren't working with you, you see, not to find yourself being aggressive, not to find yourself being in a state of contradiction with them, but finding a way in which you can work with that so that you feel you're still gently progressing.

418
00:40:28,396 --> 00:40:29,476
It's very important, that is.

419
00:40:33,456 --> 00:40:37,284
And eventually I think you find that people begin to respect you for it actually.

420
00:40:43,757 --> 00:40:48,347
So then there's finally on the Eightfold Path you've got the three which are to do with meditation.

421
00:40:49,048 --> 00:40:53,659
So it's right concentration, right effort and right mindfulness.

422
00:40:54,853 --> 00:40:57,257
When we're sitting, we have to see that as a training.

423
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:58,858
That isn't an end in itself.

424
00:40:59,460 --> 00:41:02,724
That is a place where we are developing this right effort.

425
00:41:02,804 --> 00:41:06,268
We're developing a certain type of mindfulness.

426
00:41:06,869 --> 00:41:10,273
It's a mindfulness which is geared to seeing these three characteristics.

427
00:41:10,893 --> 00:41:13,036
That doesn't negate other types of mindfulness.

428
00:41:14,157 --> 00:41:17,402
You want to be mindful of adding up your bills for a start.

429
00:41:17,382 --> 00:41:39,001
yeah it's not it's not easy but there is this other angle to our awareness to our uh to something within us which has an inkling there's an inkling there within us that you know that there may be something better than this yeah so you wouldn't be here if you if that inkling wasn't there you wouldn't be going through this misery

430
00:41:39,336 --> 00:41:49,666
a whole day of it if you didn't know that if there wasn't something in you which was suggesting that there was something other than what we're actually experiencing.

431
00:41:50,389 --> 00:41:56,757
Now, what we're doing in this meditation, remember, is separating out this very bright intelligence.

432
00:41:57,599 --> 00:42:01,362
This intelligence confuses itself with apparition.

433
00:42:01,802 --> 00:42:03,766
It confuses itself with intellect.

434
00:42:03,826 --> 00:42:10,152
It confuses itself with words, with stories, with images, with films, inner films.

435
00:42:10,873 --> 00:42:15,519
It confuses itself with emotions and how emotions express themselves in art.

436
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:20,025
It confuses itself with the body and the intelligence of the body.

437
00:42:20,932 --> 00:42:27,853
You know, these sports people, tremendous physical intelligence, you know, these gymnasts, I can't believe it.

438
00:42:27,873 --> 00:42:35,635
And those three, when we see intelligence expressing itself through that, we think that's what intelligence is.

439
00:42:35,902 --> 00:42:51,244
but it's not you see what we're discovering is this other place this knowing that is within us which is very bright very clear and is able to distance itself from all these apparitions that we call ourselves now

440
00:42:51,224 --> 00:43:20,202
it's it's recognizing that place how important that place is and being able to re-establish it throughout the day which is the trick to slowly progressing in our daily lives and not feeling that you know we're not getting anywhere even when you do this practice well you still get the feeling of not going anywhere but that's because but that's because of of expectation that there's going to be some sort of huge leap and i'm going to wake up a completely different animal

441
00:43:21,228 --> 00:43:23,753
But unfortunately it very rarely happens like that.

442
00:43:24,596 --> 00:43:25,838
It's a very slow progress.

443
00:43:25,898 --> 00:43:27,541
I mean the Buddha warns us that.

444
00:43:27,561 --> 00:43:28,864
He says it's very gradual.

445
00:43:32,172 --> 00:43:39,068
We can expect some great change over a period of 25 years if we work at it, a long term project.

446
00:43:40,043 --> 00:43:48,755
So one thing that we can do when we return home is just to write to yourself.

447
00:43:49,476 --> 00:43:54,304
Write a little letter to yourself about how you think you ought to spend the next year.

448
00:43:55,246 --> 00:43:57,409
Make small resolutions that you know you can keep.

449
00:43:57,449 --> 00:43:59,132
Don't make these big ones.

450
00:43:59,112 --> 00:44:05,681
For instance, if you don't have a habit of sitting in the morning, you know, don't say to yourself, well, from now on, it's one hour in the morning and one hour in the evening.

451
00:44:06,222 --> 00:44:07,364
You know, it lasts a day.

452
00:44:08,204 --> 00:44:09,746
And then you get fed up with yourself.

453
00:44:10,427 --> 00:44:19,179
But if you say to yourself something that you can really handle, like 10 minutes, heavens, you can spare 10 minutes of a morning and 10 minutes of an evening.

454
00:44:19,159 --> 00:44:29,648
And then very slowly the effect of that, you see, and just this constant self, this constant recollection throughout the day of coming back to that point of being aware, see.

455
00:44:30,329 --> 00:44:32,771
Even now, just to be aware right now.

456
00:44:33,612 --> 00:44:46,905
Now that awareness can be single, can be one-pointed, you could just be listening to my words, it can be spacious, you can be aware of what's happening in your body, you can be aware of your feet on the ground and still be aware of the words.

457
00:44:48,168 --> 00:44:51,032
The object of awareness is not the awareness itself.

458
00:44:51,431 --> 00:44:58,661
Sometimes you have to be very single, you know, you have to be right there with what you're doing, like when you're crossing a road or something in busy traffic.

459
00:44:59,862 --> 00:45:01,706
And at other times it can be quite spacious.

460
00:45:02,387 --> 00:45:04,489
So the situation demands it.

461
00:45:04,730 --> 00:45:09,516
But don't confuse the object of awareness with the faculty of the knowing.

462
00:45:10,797 --> 00:45:18,106
And it's that separation which brings us constantly back to this amazing thing that we have, you know, this pure intelligence.

463
00:45:19,217 --> 00:45:22,684
And remember that it's within that intelligence that the kink lies.

464
00:45:23,525 --> 00:45:25,650
That's where the delusion lies.

465
00:45:25,710 --> 00:45:28,034
It doesn't lie outside itself.

466
00:45:28,094 --> 00:45:30,860
If it was out there, you could quickly see it.

467
00:45:30,900 --> 00:45:34,266
We could probably very quickly become awakened.

468
00:45:35,068 --> 00:45:38,355
But it's within the beholding that the problem lies.

469
00:45:38,596 --> 00:45:40,398
And that's why we have to keep working at it.

470
00:45:41,273 --> 00:45:46,710
Even when we begin to have insights, we begin to see, oh yes, everything's arising and passing.

471
00:45:46,791 --> 00:45:48,958
I can see how I cause all my own suffering.

472
00:45:49,679 --> 00:45:52,971
Remember in Buddhism, nobody can cause you psychological pain.

473
00:45:53,608 --> 00:45:57,313
If you can't, you've got to get to that point where you realize that.

474
00:45:57,733 --> 00:46:02,838
But that doesn't mean to say there isn't going to be any, because there's all this backlog that you've got to work through.

475
00:46:03,420 --> 00:46:06,083
And that's all this stuff that keeps coming up throughout the day.

476
00:46:07,123 --> 00:46:17,355
So it's again this ability to stay with it, to be patient, to constantly reestablish ourselves in that position of the observation post.

477
00:46:18,043 --> 00:46:22,271
And as I say, this isn't a big effort.

478
00:46:22,512 --> 00:46:24,554
This isn't like you're climbing a mountain.

479
00:46:25,177 --> 00:46:35,014
This is a lot to do with just self-cajoling, with just talking to yourself in a right way, with persuading yourself to be there, not to get caught up in that.

480
00:46:35,554 --> 00:46:38,500
Come back, you know.

481
00:46:47,643 --> 00:47:09,820
So if we just sit quietly for a moment and just let thoughts arise and pass away.

482
00:48:00,188 --> 00:48:06,039
So I suppose the main thing I was trying to get across was the importance of reflection.

483
00:48:07,842 --> 00:48:13,112
It's just part of thinking about the way we're living, making the right decisions.

484
00:48:14,454 --> 00:48:17,420
Not just keep going on blindly.

485
00:48:26,614 --> 00:48:39,527
So I hope my words have been of some assistance and I can only wish from the depth of my heart that you become fully liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

